Package: eyedroppeR
Type: Package
Title: Extract Hex Codes by Clicking an Image
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
  c(person(given = "Daniel",
           family = "Oehm",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "danieloehm@gmail.com"))
Description: Plots an image either locally or from a URL and allows the user
    to click the image to save the hex of the pixel. User can select multiple
    colours or automatically select a user specified number of colours.
Depends: 
  R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
  ggplot2,
  purrr,
  grid,
  glue,
  seecolor,
  ggpath,
  magick,
  stringr,
  gridExtra
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/doehm/eyedroppeR
BugReports: https://github.com/doehm/eyedroppeR/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
